article_title: Blue Cross Insurers Cut Commissions On Obamacare Sales

article_metadata.description: Blue Cross and Blue Shield insurers across the country are eliminating commissions on sales of individual health plans as part of cost-cutting moves that could hurt future sales of policies under the Affordable Care Act. The moves follow last year’s high-profile decision by the nation’s largest health insurer, UnitedHealth Group, to curtail [...]
